パッケージ jp.co.rakuten.util.collection

Containers with I/F of like 'C++ STL'.

参照先:
          説明

インタフェースの概要
StdContainer<T> Basic interface of associative container.
StdIterator<T> Iterator like C++ STL.
StdMap<K,V> Associative container like std::map of C++ STL.
StdMultiMap<K,V> Associative container like std::multimap of C++ STL.
StdMultiSet<T> Associative container like std::multiset of C++ STL.
StdRandom<T,K> Random accessable base interface of associative container.
StdRandomMulti<T,K> Random accessable interface of associative container overlapping key is allowed.
StdRandomUnique<T,K> Random accessable interface of associative container overlapping key is not allowed.
StdSequence<T> Basic interface of associative container.
StdSet<T> Associative container like std::set of C++ STL.
 

クラスの概要
CompatibleIterable<T> Convert I/F from StdSequence to java.lang.Iterable.
CompatibleIterator<T> Convert I/F from StdSequence to java.lang.Iterator.
CompatibleReverseIterable<T> Convert I/F with reverse from StdSequence to java.lang.Iterable.
CompatibleReverseIterator<T> Convert I/F with reverse from StdSequence to java.lang.Iterator.
ConstStdIterator<T> Unmodifiable iterator(Wrapped StdIterator).
Pair<FIRST,SECOND> How come jdk isn't equipped with basic classes like This?

Containers with I/F of like 'C++ STL'. And wrappers to Java native iterator.
